description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for a Specialist Occupational Therapist to join the Cardio thoracics team here at University Hospital Southampton NHS Foundation Trust (UHS).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE TEAM&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By joining this team you will be part of a combined Therapy Services department of over 200 staff, consisting of B2-4 Therapy support staff, Occupational Therapists and Physiotherapists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU’LL DO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a regional Cardiothoracic centre in one of Europe’s largest teaching hospitals, we are excited to be recruiting a specialist Band 6 Occupational Therapist. This is a new role and we are looking for a dynamic and enthusiastic Occupational therapist who wishes to specialise in Cardiothoracics and heart failure to join our cohesive and experienced therapy team. This role will give you the chance to work alongside our MDT to develop our heart failure therapy service under the guidance of an advanced therapy team as well as being involved in early rehabilitation of patients from cardiac intensive care and planning of ongoing care for a variety of patients with complex rehabilitation needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will offer the opportunity to supervise band 5 staff, assist with in service training, audits and service development projects. To develop clinical and leadership skills and the ability to manage aspects of the service. Education and support is widely available both from within the therapy team, but also from the highly specialised Multidisciplinary team within the Cardiothoracic department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT WE’RE LOOKING FOR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Skills that would be ideal for this post are a good knowledge and understanding of a variety of cardiac conditions, heart failure management and confidence to assess and treat a range of neurological conditions that may result in the peri-operative period. Excellent communication skills are essential for this role to enable education to patients and relatives and allow for regular communications with other health care professionals and the MDT.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should have relevant postgraduate clinical experience (previous experience in treating patients with cardiothoracic conditions is desirable but not essential) with a commitment to develop your knowledge and skills in this field. Excellent support will be given towards continual learning and professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT WE CAN OFFER YOU&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As one of the largest acute teaching Trust’s in England, we can offer learning and development opportunities to help you achieve the career you aspire to. We believe you deserve the best possible surroundings in which to do your job and we want to support you in doing your job to the best of your ability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Trust, we support flexible working and will consider requests taking into account the needs of the service. You’ll have an opportunity to discuss this at interview. Our LiveWell and inspire programme offers opportunities, support and advice, including smoking cessation services, exercise and activity classes, and support for mental health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;UHS employees are able to access a huge range of NHS discounts, are entitled to a minimum of 35 days paid holiday (pro rata) on appointment, can access on-site nursery facilities (subject to availability), and we offer a generous pension scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT OUR TRUST AND SOUTHAMPTON&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;UHS is rated ‘Good’ by the CQC and in the latest national NHS Staff Survey, we were in the top 10 acute trusts for staff engagement and for staff recommending the hospital as a place to work or receive care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Southampton is an attractive place to live and work situated on the south coast, with an international airport and only an hour on the train from central London. The New Forest National Park and the beaches of the Jurassic coast are also right on our doorstep. The city offers living costs 20% lower than those in London, 13 schools rated outstanding by Ofsted and 13 nearby green spaces to enjoy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ADDITIONAL INFORMATION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on Thursday, 26 November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lydia Smith&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Senior Occupational Therapist&lt;/p&gt;
